snippet: Some economists are questioning whether Big Data will ever have the impact of the first Internet wave, let alone the industrial revolutions of past centuries.
abstract: News analysis; some economists are questioning predictions that say vast amount of data on the Internet will be harnessed in a way that supercharges the economy; many people have likened the harnessing of Big Data to industrial revolutions of past centuries, but there has so far been little evidence that this is the case.
lead_paragraph: Some economists are questioning whether Big Data will ever have the impact of the first Internet wave, let alone the industrial revolutions of past centuries.

headline.print_headline: Is Big Data an Economic Big Dud?
headline.main: Is Big Data an Economic Big Dud?
